  {
    "@id": "https://ticketpro.ca/event/1671961154",
    "@type": [
      "http://schema.org/Event"
    ],
    "http://schema.org/startDate": [
      {
        "@type": "http://schema.org/Date",
        "@value": "2026-04-25T19:30:00-03:00"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/location": [
      {
        "@id": "https://ticketpro.ca/place/55150121"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/image": [
      {
        "@id": "https://tproatlantic.ticketpro.ca/api/v1/resources/1671919909.jpeg?version=3"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/offers": [
      {
        "@id": "_:g790620"
      },
      {
        "@id": "_:g790640"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://ww3.ticketpro.ca/event.php?event_id=10710"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/url": [
      {
        "@id": "https://ww3.ticketpro.ca/event.php?event_id=10710"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "Green Room Session with Daniel James McFadyen"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p><b>Daniel James McFadyen</b> is an award-winning indie-folk artist whose expressive lyricism, charismatic stage presence, and road-worn storytelling have made him one of Canada's most compelling contemporary voices. His 2025 sophomore album, <b><i>Back To The Country</i></b> (LHM Records), marks a defining moment in his artistic evolution—an intimate, organic, and boldly confident full-length that leans into the Americana/Canadiana textures he has grown increasingly known for.</p>\n\n<p>Recorded live off the floor in a cabin on British Columbia's Shuswap Lake with producer <b>Cole Friesen</b>, the album captures an unpolished, lived-in warmth. Across its 11 tracks, McFadyen weaves themes of disillusionment, hope, daydreaming, heartbreak, humour, and the search for home. From the barn-burning stomp of 'Spinnaker (I'm Leavin'),' to the wistful ache of 'Hurt My Heart,' to the wry charm of 'Landmine,' <i>Back To The Country</i> showcases a songwriter stepping fully into his voice.</p>\n\n<p>McFadyen's rise has been powered equally by his dynamic, deeply interactive live shows. His cross-Canada tours have sold out major venues—including Toronto's Great Hall, Halifax's Marquee Ballroom, and Ottawa's Overflow Brewing—cultivating a devoted and ever-growing fanbase. In 2024, he earned three <b>Music Nova Scotia Awards</b>, the most of any artist that year, cementing his status as a breakout performer.</p>\n\n<p>Now in 2026, Daniel James McFadyen continues to carve out his place within the modern folk landscape—bridging heartfelt storytelling with the communal spirit of classic Canadian songwriting. With <i>Back To The Country</i> defining a new era in his sound, McFadyen stands firmly at the forefront of a new generation of Canadian troubadours</p>\n\n\n\n<style>\n.location-page-temp {display: block!important;}\n</style>\n\n"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/eventAttendanceMode": [
      {
        "@id": "http://schema.org/OfflineEventAttendanceMode"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/eventStatus": [
      {
        "@id": "http://schema.org/EventScheduled"
      }
    ]
  },
